text: Central Makira is a constituency of the Solomon Islands. It is in the Makira Province. It was created in 1993. ==Election results== 2019 general election Candidate Party Votes Nestor Ghiro Independent 3,803 Peter Thompson Usumae United Democratic Party 1,419 Hypolite Taremae Independent 152 Casper Muna Democratic Alliance Party 29 Invalid/blank votes 14 Total 5,417 Registered voters 6,299 Source: Solomon Islands Electoral Commission ==References== Category:Solomon Islands parliamentary constituencies
